  "body": "```\r\n    mapping (address => bool) private types;\r\n\r\n\r\n    function setType(address[] calldata addressesToAdd, bool value) public {\r\n        for (uint i=0; i<addressesToAdd.length; i++){\r\n            setType(addressesToAdd, value);\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function setType(address account, bool value) public {\r\n        types[account] = value;\r\n    }\r\n```\r\nThe code has an error as it should be setType(addressesToAdd[i], value);\r\nCalling setType(address[],bool) with the (wrong)code above results in:\r\n` Error: Transaction reverted and Hardhat couldn't infer the reason. Please report this to help us improve Hardhat.`\r\n\r\nExpected:\r\nHardhat notice the wrong value type is send to the 2nd function.\r\n\r\nrepo to reproduce:\r\nhttps://github.com/rube-de/hardhat-array-problem\r\n\r\n\r\n",
